<br>
Now, none of this is controversial, exciting, or even very interesting, but I think it would probably be very useful.  Post-50, wizards really come into their own.  FT items are available, nukes are way better, spec savings are high, AAs have a tremendous impact, rains are worth casting, Familiars help with mana regen, high level mind buffs make mana regen much less of an issue - in short, wizards shine.<br>
<br>
Pre-50, however, they don't.  Mana regen is a major issue, rains actually have worse ratios than regular nukes, mana regen buffs are short duration, so unconventional groups (chanter/bard-free) aren't a viable option for most wizards, despite being some of the most fun groups.<br>
<br>
My proposal would simply be to extend the Spear line of spells all the way down to level 4, with a new spear perhaps every 2 circles.  The introduction of the level 52 mini-spear (Frozen harpoon) with LoY is a good first step in this direction, and I think the process should continue.  The spear spells should do similar damage to standard nukes, but have an improved ratio compared to standard nukes of that level, and should still come at the price of a relatively long recast delay.  This should keep the &quot;mini-spears&quot; from simply replacing standard nukes, while allowing the wizard to combo-cast spells more efficiently, and to keep up reasonably well in groups at lower levels.<br>
<br>
And for the naysayers - sure, the 1-49 game can be blasted through these days (although less so soon without KEI) - but for people that enjoy leveling various alts, or simply enjoy the mid-range game, balance is just as important as it is for the 50+ crowd.<br>
<br>
<br>
Fixing the ratios on lower-level rains would be nice too.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br>  Posts: 4550<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 1:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> They would also need to be spaced far enough apart level-wise such that the old one would be obselete before you got the new one.  Otherwise you could alternate nukes which would sort of redefine the whole class.<br>
<br>
And the only other &quot;naysaying&quot; thing I can think of is that nukes with a long recast really aren't in character for a wizard in general. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganwolfxev>LoganwolfXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 4:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> Personally, I would like it better if they just got rid of the recast time on our level 60 Ice Spear.<br>
<br>
The low end game does not need new spells imo. <p>Loganwolf 65 Wizard<br>
<br>
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=626524</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=claudshadowflare>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Has Eddie Murphy's<BR>taste in women</span><br>  Posts: 3613<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 4:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> You don't remember playing a wizard from 1 to 29, do you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganwolfxev>LoganwolfXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 5:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I do.  My first character was a wizard.  I wore cloth from orc pawns until level about level 10.  At level 8 I helped a level 5 HIE cleric in GFay find her corpse, took me 2 hours.  Next thing you know, the cleric, her husband, and myself are best of friends in EQ and we logged in every night to play togeher.  My cleric friend made me a full set of Raw Silk, that lasted me until about level 25.  Then I actually started to realize that INT items were best.<br>
<br>
I remember back in CB around level 15, I was nuking the shit out of orcs and the group monk claimed I was a great wizard.  I honestly do not think I needed more power when I was a young wizard.<br>
<br>
Young wizards ARE power.  Untwinked melees cannot do nearly as much damage as a untwinked caster.<br>
<br>
So I say again, no the young wizards do not need new spells.  Especially if you are talking about soloing, make some friends, go have fun with them. <p>Loganwolf 65 Wizard<br>
<br>
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=626524</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganwolfxev>LoganwolfXev</A> at: 5/29/03 5:53:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 6:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> I think its a good idea, to the true new player (how many are there, like 2 per month serverwide?) it would help in a group were not that much dmg was needed but no nukes make the wizza look bad. <br>
<br>
I agree that young wizzas own vs melee, but twink a wizzard with 40k worth of stuff see yourself powerful twink a melee with 40k worth see yourself as a god. Sure as lvls go up it gets evened out some but melee benefit more from equipment than pure casters. <br>
<br>
F3 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 7:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> Yes, I agree, extend the line down. Even though I'm about to hit 52 and get Ice Harpoon, I think this would benifit wizards beneath me. I can see two more lower version of this spell. Maybe Ice Javilin, and Ice Dagger, (just keeping with the throwing, pointy theme) If ice dagger was the first, it should have a recast time of 13 seconds, and then adjust the casting time down as the spell line goes up, so ice spear should have a recast time of around 7 seconds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 1:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> The sub-50 spell lineup sure has a different flavor to it than 51+.  But I'm not sure I disagree with it, actually.<br>
<br>
As a younge wizard grows up, his spells all become: more efficient, more powerful, and longer-casting.  This is a reasonable progression for the road to mastery.  But boy is that casting time on Ice Comet rough.<br>
<br>
But then when you get your first draught, everything changes.  You're suddenly much more versitile.  After tons of Ice Comets, it felt *good*.<br>
<br>
The thing about the spear line is it trades recast speed (and range) for efficiency.  But really, how long would the recast have to be for it *not* to be favored over the long-cast of Ice Comet or Rend?<br>
<br>
If I were going to add to the young wizard spell lineup, personally, I'd add bolts up to 24.  Bolts provided some nice tactical options while we had them.  And once we got snare, we had other options and didnt' miss bolts too much.  But boy, 20-29 are ugly levels. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 54 Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 11:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spear Line</span><hr size=1> What would be nice is if that glut of level 60 spells was redistributed 51-59.  Sad that our biggest nuke at level 59 is still Ice Comet.  At the very least, Sunstrike could be moved down to about level 55, leaving Garrison's as the big fire Nuke at 60, Elnericks for magic, and Spear for Ice.  Ideally,  A large magic could be added 52-53'ish, Sunstrike 55-56'ish, and a Standard Large Ice at 59 to fill those annoying holes in our lineup.  Draughts are cool, but I like to see things go boom. <p><br>
